# public/ - Static Assets & SEO Files

## Purpose
Static files served as-is by Vercel. No processing.

## Files

```
public/
├── robots.txt              # Search engine directives (auto-generated at build)
├── sitemap.xml             # URL list for SEO (auto-generated at build)
├── sitemap.html            # Human-readable sitemap (optional)
├── favicon.ico             # Browser tab icon
├── apple-touch-icon.png    # iOS bookmark icon
└── images/
    ├── og-image.png        # OpenGraph default image (1200×630px)
    └── ...
```

## robots.txt

Auto-generated by `app/robots.ts` at build time.

```
User-agent: *
Allow: /
Disallow: /admin
Disallow: /_next

Sitemap: https://toolnest.com/sitemap.xml
```

## sitemap.xml

Auto-generated by `app/sitemap.ts` at build time.

Includes:
- All calculator pages (dynamic routes)
- All category pages
- Static pages (home, about, contact, etc.)
- Priority + changefreq per page type

Example:
```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<urlset xmlns="http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9">
  <url>
    <loc>https://toolnest.com/</loc>
    <priority>1.0</priority>
    <changefreq>daily</changefreq>
  </url>
  <url>
    <loc>https://toolnest.com/calculators/mortgage-calculator</loc>
    <priority>0.8</priority>
    <changefreq>monthly</changefreq>
  </url>
</urlset>
```

## Images

**favicon.ico** (16×16, 32×32, 64×64px)
- Upload to public/
- Next.js automatically finds it

**apple-touch-icon.png** (180×180px)
- iOS bookmark icon
- Optional but good for branding

**og-image.png** (1200×630px)
- OpenGraph default image
- Shows when link shared on social media
- Referenced in metadata.ts

**Images in content:**
- Store in `public/images/`
- Reference in markdown or JSON:
  ```json
  {
    "imageSrc": "/images/mortgage-example.png"
  }
  ```

## HTTPS & Security

- Vercel automatically redirects HTTP → HTTPS
- Robots.txt should reference https:// URLs
- No need for .htaccess or rewrite rules (Vercel handles)

## Performance

- Keep file sizes small (compress images with WebP)
- Lazy load images below fold (`<img loading="lazy">`)
- Use Next.js `<Image>` component (auto-optimization)

## SEO

**Never:**
- Delete or move sitemap.xml (external backlinks rely on it)
- Delete robots.txt without replacement
- Use robots.txt to hide content from users (it's public)

**Do:**
- Update sitemap priority when launching new high-value content
- Monitor Google Search Console for 404 errors in sitemap

## Adding New Files

1. Create file in public/ folder
2. Reference as `/filename` in code
   ```tsx
   <img src="/images/calculator.png" alt="..." />
   ```
3. Vercel serves at `https://toolnest.com/filename`

Example:
```
public/images/mortgage.png
→ <img src="/images/mortgage.png" />
→ https://toolnest.com/images/mortgage.png
```

## No Need for

- `/sitemap.html` (optional, not required for SEO)
- `/ads.txt` (if using AdSense, Google handles it)
- `/security.txt` (unless needed for security contact)
